        ssoorrtt(1) produces the appropriate error messages and exits with code 1;
        otherwise, ssoorrtt(1) returns 0; ssoorrtt(1) --cc produces no output.

    --mm
        Merge only; the input files are assumed to be pre-sorted.

    --oo output
        The argument given is the name of an output file to be used instead of
        the standard output. This file can be the same as one of the input
        files.

    --TT _d_i_r
