  NNOOTTEESS

    The current ssoorrtt(1) command uses lexicographic radix sorting, which
    requires that sort keys be kept in memory (as opposed to previous versions
    which used quick and merge sorts and did not). Performance therefore
    depends highly on the efficient choice of sort keys, and the --bb option and
    the field2 argument of the --kk option should be used whenever possible.
    Similarly, ssoorrtt(1) --kk11ff is equivalent to ssoorrtt(1) --ff and might take twice
    as long.

